WEBVTT

00:01.248 --> 00:02.190
FEMALE SINGER:
♪♪ IT'S A BEAUTIFUL ♪♪

00:02.290 --> 00:04.294
♪♪ IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY ♪♪

00:06.500 --> 00:08.764
♪♪ IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY... ♪♪

00:08.864 --> 00:11.650
BILLY: OH.
OLIVIA: HERE WE GO. OK.

00:11.750 --> 00:13.494
WHAT IS--
WHAT IS THIS?

00:13.594 --> 00:15.540
WELL, IT'S BLUEBERRY
AND RICOTTA TOAST.

00:15.640 --> 00:17.584
BLUEBERRY AND RICOTTA.
WHAT--

00:17.684 --> 00:18.946
WHAT HAPPENED TO
THE EGGS AND THE

00:19.046 --> 00:20.230
CRACKLIN' BACON AND--

00:20.330 --> 00:21.793
I THINK IT LOOKS
GREAT, HONEY.

00:21.894 --> 00:23.436
- IT TASTES GREAT, TOO.
- YOU SEE, DAD?

00:23.536 --> 00:25.481
JORDAN'S INHALING HIS.
BILLY: OK.

00:25.582 --> 00:27.004
DAD, IF YOU DON'T WANT YOURS,
I CAN TAKE IT OFF YOUR PLATE.

00:27.104 --> 00:28.848
EXCUSE ME.
GREEDY WITH YOUR--

00:28.948 --> 00:30.952
[LAURA GIGGLES]
BILLY: LET ME--ALL RIGHT.

00:32.838 --> 00:34.742
OLIVIA: MM. WELL?

00:34.842 --> 00:36.786
I STAND CORRECTED.
THIS IS DELICIOUS.

00:36.886 --> 00:38.390
OLIVIA: I KNOW.
BILLY: ALL RIGHT.

00:38.490 --> 00:40.274
WAY TO GO. MM.

00:40.374 --> 00:41.877
SO, HAVE YOU, UH,

00:41.978 --> 00:44.122
DECIDED WHAT YOU'RE GONNA
SAY TO YOUR TEAM TODAY?

00:44.222 --> 00:46.206
I'M, UH, STILL
WORKING ON IT.

00:46.306 --> 00:48.050
OLIVIA: WAIT, WHAT'S THAT?
JORDAN: MM.

00:48.150 --> 00:50.096
AFTER TODAY'S
SPRING COMBINE,
DAD'S GONNA TELL

00:50.196 --> 00:52.140
HIS TEAM THAT HE'S
LEAVING CRENSHAW
FOR THE GAU JOB.

00:52.240 --> 00:54.264
OLIVIA: HOW DO YOU THINK
THEY'LL TAKE IT?
BILLY: I DON'T KNOW.

00:54.364 --> 00:56.790
COACHING CHANGE
AT THIS LEVEL, THEY HIT
A LITTLE BIT HARDER, SO...

00:56.890 --> 00:59.236
OLIVIA: MM.
BILLY: THE PLAYERS LOOK
AT ME AS A FATHER FIGURE.

00:59.336 --> 01:01.560
GRACE IS GONNA BE THERE...
JORDAN: MM-HMM.

01:01.660 --> 01:03.184
BILLY: IF THE PLAYERS
NEED HELP AFTERWARDS.
JORDAN: AND I'LL BE THERE.

01:03.264 --> 01:05.048
BILLY: YES.
OLIVIA: WHY ARE YOU GOING?

01:05.148 --> 01:07.092
BECAUSE BEVERLY PLAYERS
ARE GONNA BE THERE.

01:07.192 --> 01:08.776
I'M GONNA HELP OUT
WITH THE DRILLS,
YOU KNOW, THROWING

01:08.876 --> 01:10.140
TO THE WIDE RECEIVERS.
BILLY: HMM. YOU THINK

01:10.240 --> 01:11.903
ANYBODY ELSE WOULD
WANT TO HELP OUT,

01:12.004 --> 01:13.707
LIKE--LIKE SPENCER?
I KNOW THE PLAYERS
LOOK UP TO HIM.

01:13.808 --> 01:15.712
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
LAURA: BABE.

01:15.812 --> 01:17.636
BILLY: HMM?
LAURA: IF YOU WANT
TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT

01:17.736 --> 01:19.280
WITH SPENCER,
JUST CALL HIM.

01:19.380 --> 01:21.524
TAKE THE FIRST STEP.

01:21.624 --> 01:23.770
OLIVIA: WELL, I'M GLAD
YOU LIKED THE BLUEBERRY
AND RICOTTA TOAST...

01:23.870 --> 01:25.774
JORDAN: MM-HMM.
OLIVIA: BUT I CAN'T
TAKE ALL THE CREDIT

01:25.874 --> 01:27.658
BECAUSE IT'S LAYLA'S RECIPE.
JORDAN: HMM. WHAT?

01:27.758 --> 01:29.302
REALLY?
NEVER MADE THIS FOR ME.

01:29.402 --> 01:31.306
WHY WOULD LAYLA
MAKE YOU BREAKFAST?

01:31.406 --> 01:33.832
BECAUSE WE'RE FRIENDS.

01:33.932 --> 01:35.956
LAURA: YOU GUYS,
I MISSED THIS,

01:36.056 --> 01:38.040
THE FOUR OF US.
BILLY: YEAH. THIS IS NICE.

01:38.140 --> 01:39.764
WE SHOULD DO THIS
MORE OFTEN.

01:39.864 --> 01:41.528
OLIVIA: I'M IN.
JORDAN: ME, TOO.

01:41.628 --> 01:43.132
LAURA: YEAH?
OLIVIA: YEAH.

01:43.232 --> 01:44.696
LAURA: SO, LIKE, WHAT?
ONCE A WEEK?

01:44.796 --> 01:46.540
OLIVIA: UHH...
JORDAN: WELL...

01:46.640 --> 01:48.182
BILLY: HA HA HA!
OLIVIA: I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT.

01:48.282 --> 01:51.070
LAURA, CHUCKLING:
OK, HOW 'BOUT...

01:51.170 --> 01:54.276
ONCE A MONTH,
JUST US?

01:54.376 --> 01:56.240
OK? THEN IT'S SETTLED.

01:56.340 --> 01:59.248
ONCE A MONTH, BREAKFAST
WITH MY FAVOURITE TEAM.

01:59.348 --> 02:01.532
LAURA: YEAH.
BILLY: ALL RIGHT. BRING IT IN.

02:01.632 --> 02:04.318
LAURA: CHEERS.
BILLY: YEAH, BAKER BREAKFAST.

02:11.774 --> 02:14.080
COOP: WAIT,
SO LIV DOESN'T WANT
TO BE FRIENDS?

02:14.180 --> 02:16.404
NAW, SHE WANTS TO BE
MORE THAN FRIENDS.

02:16.504 --> 02:18.730
BRO, BUT Y'ALL
TRIED THAT ALREADY
AND IT DIDN'T WORK.

02:18.830 --> 02:21.536
"DIDN'T WORK" IS
A LITTLE OVERSIMPLIFIED,
BUT I GUESS.

02:21.636 --> 02:22.940
NOW, LOOK, DO YOU
STILL LOVE LIV?

02:23.040 --> 02:25.464
YES. BUT AM I STILL
IN LOVE WITH HER?

02:25.564 --> 02:27.108
I DON'T KNOW.

02:27.208 --> 02:29.354
HOW DO I KNOW WHAT I FEEL
WHEN I'M AROUND HER

02:29.454 --> 02:31.878
ISN'T JUST ECHOES
FROM WHAT WE HAD?

02:31.978 --> 02:34.364
THOSE ARE GOOD QUESTIONS.
WHAT DID ALICIA SAY?

02:34.464 --> 02:35.968
SPENCER: HUH?
COOP: "HUH"?

02:36.068 --> 02:37.812
WHAT DID YOUR
CURRENT GIRLFRIEND SAY

02:37.912 --> 02:39.616
ABOUT YOUR EX-GIRLFRIEND
WANTING YOU BACK?

02:39.716 --> 02:41.260
SPENCER: I AIN'T TELL HER.
COOP: WHAT?

02:41.360 --> 02:42.823
[SCOFFS]
WHAT? LOOK, I'M TOO BUSY

02:42.923 --> 02:44.426
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT TO SAY TO LIV,

02:44.526 --> 02:45.990
WHO I'M KINDA
AVOIDING RIGHT NOW

02:46.090 --> 02:47.674
'CAUSE SHE WANTS
TO MEET UP TODAY.

02:47.774 --> 02:49.878
BRO, THERE'S WAY
TOO MUCH HISTORY
BETWEEN YOU TWO

02:49.978 --> 02:52.524
FOR YOU TO JUST BE
BLOWING HER OFF
LIKE THAT, SO IF YOU

02:52.624 --> 02:56.352
ARE GONNA AVOID HER,
YOU BETTER HAVE
A LEGIT REASON.

03:03.608 --> 03:06.254
[SIGHS QUIETLY]

03:07.898 --> 03:09.802
ARE YOU WEARING
A CARDIGAN?

03:09.902 --> 03:12.768
NO, IT'S AN OFFICIAL
COASTAL CALIFORNIA
SWEATER VEST.

03:12.868 --> 03:14.172
YOU'RE GONNA WEAR IT
TO THE COMBINE?

03:14.272 --> 03:15.534
WELL, NOW I'M
NOT SO SURE.

03:15.634 --> 03:18.902
IT'S FINE.
YOU LOOK COACH-Y.

03:19.002 --> 03:20.906
ASHER: THAT'S WHAT
I WAS GOING FOR.
JAYMEE: GOOD, GOOD.

03:21.006 --> 03:22.710
[BOTH CHUCKLE]
ASHER: ALL RIGHT.

03:22.810 --> 03:24.474
WISH ME LUCK.
[SIGHS]

03:24.574 --> 03:25.998
YOU'RE LEAVING
RIGHT NOW?

03:26.098 --> 03:27.802
YEAH, IT'S--IT'S
A LONG DRIVE. WHY?

03:27.902 --> 03:29.886
NOTHING. I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU

03:29.986 --> 03:32.112
ABOUT SOMETHING,
BUT IT CAN WAIT.

03:37.564 --> 03:39.468
IS EVERYTHING OK?

03:39.568 --> 03:42.114
I GUESS THAT DEPENDS
ON YOUR REACTION.

03:42.214 --> 03:43.556
TO WHAT?

03:43.656 --> 03:45.660
I'M PREGNANT.

03:49.108 --> 03:51.814
NOW THAT I HAVE YOUR REACTION,
ASK ME AGAIN HOW I'M DOING.

03:51.914 --> 03:54.420
NO, I'M--
I'M--I'M SORRY.

03:54.520 --> 03:57.026
OK, UM...

03:57.126 --> 03:58.990
LET ME CALL
THE OTHER COACHES,

03:59.090 --> 04:00.994
LET 'EM KNOW THAT I CAN'T
COVER THE COMBINE, OK?

04:01.094 --> 04:03.560
WE HAVE PLENTY
OF TIME TO TALK.

04:03.660 --> 04:06.166
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT PLENTY, BUT

04:06.266 --> 04:08.130
WE HAVE TIME.

04:08.230 --> 04:10.616
YOU SHOULD GO
TO THE COMBINE,

04:10.716 --> 04:13.222
WEAR YOUR LITTLE CARDIGAN.
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

04:13.322 --> 04:15.908
ASHER: SWEATER VEST.
JAYMEE: HEH! YEAH. HEH!

04:16.008 --> 04:18.092
WE CAN TALK
WHEN YOU GET BACK.

04:20.096 --> 04:21.760
[R&B MUSIC PLAYING]

04:21.860 --> 04:23.966
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

04:24.066 --> 04:26.812
LAYLA: DAD.
HEY, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE IN TOWN.

04:26.912 --> 04:30.460
HEY, UM, I'D LIKE TO SPEAK
WITH MY DAUGHTER ALONE, PLEASE?

04:30.560 --> 04:32.504
MAN: YEAH, NO PROBLEM.
[MUSIC STOPS]

04:32.604 --> 04:33.827
OK.

04:33.927 --> 04:35.872
WELL, I CAN TELL
YOU'RE UPSET,

04:35.972 --> 04:37.876
BUT CAN I HUG YOU
AT LEAST?

04:37.976 --> 04:40.020
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN MONTHS. HEH!

04:41.504 --> 04:44.250
MMM. LOOK, I'M SURE
YOU KNOW WHY I'M HERE.

04:44.350 --> 04:46.736
UM, 'CAUSE CLAY GAVE US
OUR NAME BACK?

04:46.836 --> 04:48.338
[SIGHS]

04:48.438 --> 04:50.944
EVERYTHING I BUILT
AT KEATING RECORDS,

04:51.044 --> 04:55.034
MY LIFE'S WORK, IT'S GONE.
LAYLA: WELL, THE MUSIC
CATALOGUE'S STILL THERE.

04:55.134 --> 04:58.160
WITH SOMEBODY ELSE'S
NAME ATTACHED TO IT.
IT WAS CREATED WITH MY NAME.

04:58.260 --> 05:00.566
RIGHT. WELL, IF THE NAME
MEANT SO MUCH TO YOU,

05:00.666 --> 05:03.612
MAYBE YOU SHOULD'VE
LEFT IT TO SOMEONE
WHO SHARED THAT NAME.

05:03.712 --> 05:05.616
I SHOULD'VE BEEN
YOUR LEGACY, DAD,

05:05.716 --> 05:07.702
NOT CLAY,
AND I FIXED THAT.

05:07.802 --> 05:10.428
HEY, I'M YOUR BLOOD
AND THE LEGACY
WILL CARRY ON.

05:10.528 --> 05:12.432
YOU WERE SO ADAMANT
ABOUT WANTING TO BUILD
YOUR OWN THING, I DIDN'T

05:12.532 --> 05:14.958
EVEN KNOW YOU WANTED
THE COMPANY, AND I
APOLOGISE FOR THAT.

05:15.058 --> 05:17.924
BUT I WORKED REALLY HARD
TO BUILD KEATING RECORDS
FROM SCRATCH.

05:18.024 --> 05:22.012
YES, YOU ARE MY LEGACY,
BUT SO IS THAT COMPANY,

05:22.112 --> 05:25.661
AT LEAST UNTIL SOMEONE
STRIPPED MY NAME FROM IT.

05:25.761 --> 05:28.507
[SIGHS]
SORRY.

05:28.608 --> 05:31.874
ONE DAY
YOU'LL UNDERSTAND.

05:31.974 --> 05:34.380
[FOOTSTEPS RETREAT,
LAYLA SIGHS]

05:36.826 --> 05:39.371
PREACH: A.J., WHERE YOU GOIN'?
A.J.: DETENTION.

05:39.471 --> 05:41.576
PREACH: UH,
DETENTION IS THAT WAY.
A.J.: I'MMA HIT UP

05:41.676 --> 05:43.941
THE CANDY MACHINE FIRST.
PREACH: THE CANDY MACHINE
IN THE TEACHERS' LOUNGE?

05:44.042 --> 05:46.386
A.J.: AIN'T NO TEACHERS
HERE ON SATURDAY.
PREACH: I'M HERE.

05:46.486 --> 05:49.794
LOOK, IT'S MY JOB TO
MAKE SURE THAT YOU GET
TO DETENTION ON TIME,

05:49.894 --> 05:53.682
BUT YOU GOT 20 SECONDS.
19, 18,

05:53.782 --> 05:55.526
17.
AMINA: HI, DADDY.

05:55.626 --> 05:57.892
[CHUCKLING]
AMINA, WHAT YOU DOIN' HERE?

05:57.992 --> 06:00.096
I DON'T GET YOU
UNTIL NEXT WEEKEND.

06:00.196 --> 06:03.504
MEMA DROPPED ME OFF
EARLY, SO WE CAN SPEND
THE WEEKEND TOGETHER.

06:03.604 --> 06:05.468
NICE.
LOOK, I HAVE TO, UH,

06:05.568 --> 06:07.112
SUPERVISE THIS
DETENTION THING,

06:07.212 --> 06:09.076
BUT YOU CAN HANG OUT
IN BILLY'S OFFICE.

06:09.176 --> 06:10.600
COOP IS MEETING ME
HERE FOR LUNCH.

06:10.700 --> 06:12.123
SHE'LL BE GLAD
TO SEE YOU.

06:12.223 --> 06:14.368
COME HERE, BABY GIRL.
MM.

06:14.468 --> 06:17.054
MM. I MISS YOU.

06:17.154 --> 06:18.898
WORKING
ANOTHER SATURDAY.

06:18.998 --> 06:21.584
HUH. JUST DOING
SOME RESEARCH.

06:21.684 --> 06:23.348
DID YOU HEAR
THE BIG NEWS?

06:23.448 --> 06:25.352
OLIVIA: MM-MM.
CHRISTEL: YOUR ARTICLE

06:25.452 --> 06:27.878
HAS BEEN PICKED UP
IN 8 MAJOR NEWS MARKETS.

06:27.978 --> 06:29.521
DETROIT, ATLANTA, PHILLY.

06:29.622 --> 06:31.245
A LOCAL MORNING SHOW
IN CHICAGO IS EVEN

06:31.345 --> 06:33.049
RUNNING AN ON-AIR
SEGMENT ABOUT IT.

06:33.149 --> 06:35.334
OLIVIA: WAIT. SERIOUSLY?
CHRISTEL: CONGRATULATIONS.

06:35.434 --> 06:37.619
IT'S TOO BAD I HAD TO
TURN DOWN THE INTERVIEW,

06:37.719 --> 06:40.746
BUT THIS IS STILL
HUGE FOR YOU, AND US.

06:40.846 --> 06:43.272
UH, WAIT--WHAT--UH,
WHAT INTERVIEW?

06:43.372 --> 06:45.076
THEY WANTED TO TALK
TO THE JOURNALIST

06:45.176 --> 06:46.920
WHO WROTE THE ARTICLE--
JAYDEN DAVIS.

06:47.020 --> 06:49.004
[SIGHS]
TSK.

06:49.104 --> 06:51.810
SUCKS THAT I DON'T
GET ANY CREDIT
FOR MY OWN ARTICLE.

06:51.910 --> 06:54.015
YOU CHOSE TO GO
THE PSEUDONYM ROUTE.

06:54.116 --> 06:56.220
BUT EVERYONE HERE
KNOWS WHO WROTE IT.

06:56.320 --> 06:58.766
BIG THINGS ARE COMING
TO YOU, LIV.
OLIVIA: MM.

07:05.140 --> 07:06.602
YOU'RE FEELING GUILTY,
AREN'T YOU?

07:06.702 --> 07:09.168
MY DAD JUST LOOKED
SO HEARTBROKEN.

07:09.268 --> 07:11.253
SO WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

07:11.353 --> 07:13.818
LAYLA: I GUESS TALK TO CLAY.
JORDAN: MM.

07:13.918 --> 07:16.384
I--I DON'T LIKE THE IDEA
OF YOU HAVING TO GROVEL.

07:16.484 --> 07:19.030
WHO SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT GROVELING?

07:19.130 --> 07:20.353
NOT ME.

07:20.453 --> 07:21.876
YEAH, I DON'T GROVEL.

07:21.976 --> 07:23.840
JORDAN: OF COURSE NOT.
LAYLA: YEAH. HEH!

07:23.940 --> 07:25.524
JORDAN: YOU DON'T GROVEL. NO.
LAYLA: HEY.

07:25.624 --> 07:27.008
RELAX. Y'ALL KNOW
YA AIN'T GOTTA

07:27.108 --> 07:28.450
PRETEND IN FRONT
OF ME NO MORE.

07:28.550 --> 07:30.094
UH, SORRY.
FORCE OF HABIT.

07:30.194 --> 07:31.698
JORDAN: RIGHT.
LAYLA: I SHOULD GET GOING.

07:31.798 --> 07:33.342
YEAH. I GOTTA GET
OUTTA HERE, TOO, SO...

07:33.442 --> 07:35.226
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.
BYE, SPENCE.

07:35.326 --> 07:36.869
SPENCER: LATER.
LAYLA: BYE.

07:36.970 --> 07:38.432
JORDAN: ACTUALLY, YO, SPENCE.
SPENCER: YEAH?

07:38.532 --> 07:40.076
I AM HELPING OUT AT
THE SPRING COMBINE TODAY.

07:40.176 --> 07:41.440
YOU KNOW, JUST GIVING
SOME HIGH SCHOOL JUNIORS

07:41.540 --> 07:43.083
A CHANCE TO SHINE.
DON'T SUPPOSE MAYBE

07:43.183 --> 07:44.646
YOU'D WANT TO PITCH IN AND--
SPENCER: YES.

07:44.746 --> 07:46.050
YES, DEFINITELY.
LET'S DO IT.

07:46.150 --> 07:48.615
REALLY? OK, THAT WAS
UNEXPECTEDLY EASY.

07:48.715 --> 07:50.540
WELL, I KINDA NEED
SOMETHING LEGIT
TO DO TODAY

07:50.640 --> 07:52.704
TO GET OUT
OF SOMETHING ELSE,
SO THIS IS PERFECT.

07:52.804 --> 07:54.868
MUST BE SOMETHING
YOU REALLY WANT
TO GET OUT OF BADLY

07:54.968 --> 07:57.034
IF YOU'RE WILLING
TO SPEND TIME WITH MY DAD.

07:57.134 --> 07:59.439
WHO SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT SPENDING TIME
WITH YOUR DAD? NO.

07:59.539 --> 08:01.644
NO, IT'S A BIG FIELD,
AND I'M THERE

08:01.744 --> 08:04.390
FOR THE PLAYERS,
NOT HIM. COME ON.

08:05.872 --> 08:07.878
OK.

08:13.048 --> 08:15.554
BILLY: HEY, ASH.
ASHER: HEH!

08:15.654 --> 08:17.558
BILLY: WHAT'S UP?
ASHER: HEY, COACH.

08:17.658 --> 08:19.523
AREN'T YOU GOING
TO THE COMBINE?

08:19.623 --> 08:22.008
YEAH. YEAH, I'M--
I'M ON MY WAY
THERE NOW.

08:22.108 --> 08:25.376
BILLY: OK.
ASHER: I JUST WANTED
TO GET SOME ADVICE.

08:25.476 --> 08:27.781
OH. OK.
CAN WE DISCUSS IT
AT THE COMBINE?

08:27.882 --> 08:30.427
MY GIRLFRIEND IS
PREGNANT, COACH.

08:30.527 --> 08:33.474
BILLY: OK.
[ASHER EXHALES]

08:33.574 --> 08:35.558
WOW.

08:35.658 --> 08:37.763
[EXHALES]
THAT IS THE FIRST TIME

08:37.863 --> 08:40.128
THAT I'VE
SAID IT OUT LOUD.
IT FEELS, UH--

08:40.228 --> 08:43.255
BILLY: HEH HEH!
YEAH, IT LOOKS LIKE IT.
ASHER: COACH, I HAVE...

08:43.356 --> 08:45.260
A HUNDRED QUESTIONS

08:45.360 --> 08:47.224
AND NOT ONE
SINGLE ANSWER.

08:47.324 --> 08:49.710
BILLY: YOU'LL BE READY.
ASHER: HOW DO YOU KNOW?

08:49.810 --> 08:52.716
BECAUSE YOU'RE THE MOST
PREPARED PLAYER
I'VE EVER COACHED,

08:52.816 --> 08:55.462
SO, WE'RE GONNA BE
JUST FINE.

08:56.945 --> 08:58.810
OK?

08:58.910 --> 09:01.014
NOW, WE GONNA GO
TO THIS COMBINE

09:01.114 --> 09:03.139
OR WE'RE GONNA TALK
ABOUT YOUR KID ALL DAY?

09:03.239 --> 09:04.742
[SIGHS]
YEAH, SORRY.

09:04.842 --> 09:07.028
BILLY: OK.
ASHER: UH, HEH!

09:07.128 --> 09:09.272
I'LL, UH, I'LL SEE YOU THERE.
BILLY: OK, YEAH.

09:09.372 --> 09:11.678
ALL RIGHT, UM,
THAT'S THE KITCHEN,
IT'S THAT DIRECTION.

09:11.778 --> 09:15.726
SO YOU'RE IN NO CONDITION
TO DRIVE, SO WHY DON'T WE
TAKE THE CRENSHAW BUS TOGETHER?

09:15.826 --> 09:17.370
ASHER: YEAH.
BILLY: YEAH. THERE WE GO.

09:17.470 --> 09:19.374
ASHER: YEAH, THANKS.
BILLY: THIS WAY.

09:19.474 --> 09:21.339
OPEN UP. THERE WE GO.
ASHER: YEAH.

09:21.439 --> 09:23.303
YO, WHERE DID YOU
GET THESE?

09:23.404 --> 09:25.228
WE GOT A SNACK MACHINE
IN THE TEACHERS' LOUNGE.

09:25.328 --> 09:27.272
DAWG, I JUST
BROKE MY TOOTH.

09:27.372 --> 09:29.236
THIS THING GOTTA BE,
LIKE, 30 YEARS OLD.

09:29.336 --> 09:31.562
AMINA: TASTES GOOD TO ME.
COOP: WELL, THEN, SEE HERE.

09:31.662 --> 09:34.488
YOU CAN HAVE MINE THEN.
WOMAN: AMINA.

09:34.588 --> 09:36.492
[SIGHS]

09:36.592 --> 09:39.058
WHAT DID I TELL YOU ABOUT
EATING THAT MUCH SUGAR?

09:39.158 --> 09:41.062
YOU SAID IT'LL
ROT MY TEETH.

09:41.162 --> 09:43.147
UH, YOU NEED
SOMETHING,
MRS. MOORE?

09:43.247 --> 09:45.191
YES. I NEED
MY GRANDDAUGHTER.

09:45.292 --> 09:48.599
ARE YOU FORGETTING WE HAVE
FULL CUSTODY OF HER?
THIS WAS STUPID.

09:48.699 --> 09:51.445
WHY DID YOU DROP HER OFF
EARLY IF YOU WAS GONNA
COME AT HIM LIKE THIS?

09:51.545 --> 09:53.209
THE JUDGE IS GONNA
HEAR ABOUT THIS.

09:53.309 --> 09:54.973
IT'S NOT HIS FAULT.

09:55.073 --> 09:56.696
I RAN AWAY.

09:56.796 --> 09:58.902
COOP: WAIT. WHAT?
AMINA: I'M SORRY, MEMA.

09:59.002 --> 10:01.347
I LIED AND SAID YOU
DROPPED ME OFF EARLY
'CAUSE I DON'T WANT

10:01.447 --> 10:03.512
TO MOVE TO BALTIMORE.
COOP: BALTIMORE?

10:03.612 --> 10:05.276
AIN'T NOBODY GOIN'
TO BALTIMORE.

10:05.376 --> 10:07.120
WE ARE.
WE'RE MOVING THERE

10:07.220 --> 10:09.044
AT THE END OF AMINA'S
SCHOOL SEMESTER.

10:09.144 --> 10:11.449
THE HELL YOU ARE.

10:11.549 --> 10:14.376
AMINA, LET'S GO
CHECK OUT THE GYM.

10:14.476 --> 10:16.420
IS THIS THE PART
WHERE YOU GET ALL TOUGH

10:16.520 --> 10:18.825
AND YOU TRY TO
INTIMIDATE ME?

10:18.926 --> 10:21.672
NO, IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

10:21.772 --> 10:23.676
AMINA'S
OUR RESPONSIBILITY,

10:23.776 --> 10:25.680
AND SHE'S BETTER OFF
WITHOUT YOU.

10:25.780 --> 10:29.248
I KNOW THE REAL YOU.
I WATCHED YOU GROW UP
ON THESE STREETS,

10:29.348 --> 10:32.375
AND THAT'S WHY
I'M TAKING HER
FAR AWAY FROM HERE,

10:32.475 --> 10:35.121
AND NOW YOU DON'T
GET HER NEXT WEEKEND.

10:38.930 --> 10:40.834
JORDAN:
OK, SO REWIND.

10:40.934 --> 10:43.038
MY SISTER ASKED YOU
TO GET BACK TOGETHER?

10:43.138 --> 10:45.684
SPENCER: YEP.
JORDAN: AND YOU
DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING?

10:45.784 --> 10:47.728
SHE AIN'T GIVE ME
A CHANCE.

10:47.828 --> 10:49.573
BUT SHE WANTED
TO TALK TODAY
AND INSTEAD,

10:49.673 --> 10:51.256
YOU'RE DOING THE COMBINE?
SPENCER: BRO,

10:51.356 --> 10:53.582
YOU ASKED ME
FOR MY HELP.

10:53.682 --> 10:56.027
NAH. YOU ARE JUST
AVOIDING HER.
THAT IS NOT COOL.

10:56.127 --> 10:59.074
SPENCER: WHOSE SIDE
ARE YOU ON, DAWG?
JORDAN: MY SISTER'S.

10:59.174 --> 11:01.158
OK, LOOK, COOL.

11:01.258 --> 11:03.162
YOU WANT ME
TO LEAVE, I'LL LEAVE.
JORDAN: NO, NO, NO, NO.

11:03.262 --> 11:05.969
COME ON. WE'RE ALREADY
HERE, ALL RIGHT?
BESIDES, YOU PROBABLY

11:06.069 --> 11:08.735
ALREADY BLEW IT
WITH LIV, BUT MY DAD WAS
GLAD YOU AGREED TO COME.

11:08.835 --> 11:11.782
SPENCER: WHY'D YOU TELL HIM?
JORDAN: 'CAUSE IT WAS HIS IDEA.

11:11.882 --> 11:13.946
HE ASKED YOU
TO BRING ME HERE?

11:14.046 --> 11:16.712
I MEAN, HE MENTIONED IT.
IT WASN'T LIKE IT WAS
SOME DEVIOUS PLAN.

11:16.812 --> 11:18.516
BRO, NOW HE'S GONNA
THINK I'M ACCEPTING

11:18.616 --> 11:20.320
SOME OLIVE BRANCH THAT
I AIN'T READY FOR YET.

11:20.420 --> 11:21.924
YOU GOTTA RELAX,
DUDE, OK?

11:22.024 --> 11:24.008
YOU ARE THE ONE WHO IS
MAKING EVERYTHING

11:24.108 --> 11:27.316
MORE COMPLICATED HERE,
ALL RIGHT, WITH OLIVIA
AND MY DAD.

11:31.084 --> 11:33.770
I'MMA GO CHECK OUT
THESE WIDE RECEIVERS.

11:37.698 --> 11:39.743
[SIGHS]
I...

11:43.270 --> 11:45.936
CLAY, CHUCKLING:
YEAH, THIS LOOKS GOOD.
I LIKE THAT.

11:46.036 --> 11:48.943
[SIGHS]
YOU DIDN'T
WASTE ANY TIME.

11:49.044 --> 11:51.950
REBRANDING IS OUR
MAIN FOCUS RIGHT NOW.

11:52.050 --> 11:55.398
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
LAYLA: CLAY TAYLOR
ENTERTAINMENT?

11:55.498 --> 11:58.003
YOU REALLY GOING
WITH THE INITIALS?
CLAY: IT'S OUR NEW LOGO. WHY?

11:58.104 --> 11:59.847
LAYLA: CTE?
CLAY: MM-HMM.

11:59.948 --> 12:01.772
YOU KNOW THAT'S
A SPORTS INJURY-RELATED

12:01.872 --> 12:02.974
BRAIN CONDITION, RIGHT?

12:03.074 --> 12:04.658
CAN I HELP YOU
WITH SOMETHING?

12:04.758 --> 12:07.103
YES, ACTUALLY.
GOOD NEWS.

12:07.204 --> 12:09.588
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO USE THE CTE LOGO.

12:09.688 --> 12:11.794
IT'S CLAY TAYLOR
ENTERTAINMENT.

12:11.894 --> 12:14.279
LAYLA: NO, IT'S KEATING RECORDS.
CLAY: WHAT?

12:14.379 --> 12:16.324
YOU CAN HAVE
THE NAME BACK.

12:16.424 --> 12:18.288
I WAS WRONG.

12:18.388 --> 12:20.492
DO YOU REALLY THINK
YOU WERE WRONG,

12:20.592 --> 12:22.658
OR DID DADDY SAY
YOU WERE WRONG?

12:22.758 --> 12:25.263
DOES IT MATTER?
YOU CAN HAVE
THE NAME BACK.

12:25.363 --> 12:29.072
CONGRATULATIONS. YOU WIN.
CLAY: I ALREADY WON.

12:29.172 --> 12:31.517
I GOT THE ARTISTS,
THE CATALOGUE,
AND THE EMPIRE.

12:31.617 --> 12:34.162
NOW IT'S ALL UNDER MY NAME.
LAYLA: CTE.

12:34.262 --> 12:36.368
IT'S CLAY TAYLOR
ENTERTAI--

12:36.468 --> 12:39.254
LOOK, THE BALL IS
ALREADY ROLLING
ON THIS REBRANDING.

12:39.354 --> 12:41.499
IT'S TOO LATE,
SO YOU CAN KEEP
THE KEATING NAME.

12:41.599 --> 12:43.744
NOW GO WORK
ON THEM DADDY ISSUES
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

12:43.844 --> 12:46.710
I HAVE AN EMPIRE
TO RUN HERE.
[CLICKS TEETH]

12:46.810 --> 12:49.356
D, LET ME HOLLER
AT YOU RIGHT QUICK.
THIS LOOKS GOOD, MAN.

12:49.456 --> 12:52.864
MAYBE WE CAN GET
ANOTHER SIGN RIGHT HERE...
[LAYLA SIGHS]

12:54.307 --> 12:56.211
CRENSHAW GOT SOME
CRAZY TALENT
COMING BACK

12:56.311 --> 12:58.536
NEXT YEAR, COACH.
BILLY: HEH HEH! YES, SIR.

12:58.636 --> 13:00.581
SHAME I AIN'T GONNA BE
OUT THERE WITH 'EM.

13:00.681 --> 13:02.665
OH, COME ON, NOW.

13:02.766 --> 13:04.870
YOU KNOW YOU'RE
GONNA BE BALLIN'
OUT THERE AT COASTAL.

13:04.970 --> 13:07.356
JABARI: HMM.
BILLY: ONLY BIGGER AND
BETTER THINGS FOR YOU, SON.

13:07.456 --> 13:09.160
JABARI: WHAT ABOUT YOU?
BILLY: HMM?

13:09.260 --> 13:11.204
BIGGER AND BETTER THINGS
IN YOUR FUTURE, TOO?

13:11.304 --> 13:13.248
THERE'S A LOT OF SMOKE
ABOUT YOU LEAVING...
BILLY: YEAH.

13:13.348 --> 13:15.253
SO GUYS ARE STARTING
TO ASK QUESTIONS.

13:15.353 --> 13:16.856
BILLY: I'MMA TELL
THE TEAM TODAY.
JABARI: WELL, WHATEVER

13:16.956 --> 13:19.422
YOU DECIDE, COACH,
I GOT YOUR BACK

13:19.522 --> 13:22.308
'CAUSE, I MEAN,
WITHOUT YOU...

13:22.408 --> 13:24.954
IF I DIDN'T
COME PLAY FOR YOU,

13:25.054 --> 13:28.602
THERE WOULD BE NO BIGGER
AND BETTER IN MY FUTURE.

13:28.702 --> 13:30.647
COME ON, MAN.

13:30.747 --> 13:33.012
I'LL NEVER FORGET
EVERYTHING YOU DID
FOR ME, COACH.

13:33.112 --> 13:35.618
I APPRECIATE THAT.

13:35.718 --> 13:38.023
THANK YOU, SON.

13:38.123 --> 13:40.028
GET OUTTA HERE.

13:40.128 --> 13:42.673
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

13:42.774 --> 13:44.878
HEY, COACH.

13:44.978 --> 13:46.682
OH, IT'S MY HUSBAND'S
ACE RECRUITER.

13:46.782 --> 13:48.406
HEH HEH.
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

13:48.506 --> 13:50.410
I MEAN, YOU WERE
MY SECRET WEAPON

13:50.510 --> 13:52.615
AND NOW YOU'RE HIS.
ASHER, CHUCKLING: YEAH, RIGHT.

13:52.715 --> 13:54.780
YOU JUST HAD
ANOTHER GREAT SEASON
AT BEVERLY WITHOUT ME.

13:54.880 --> 13:58.027
AH, WELL, WHEN YOU
WERE BY MY SIDE, IT WAS
DEFINITELY A LOT EASIER.

13:58.127 --> 14:00.713
ASHER: I DO WANT
TO KNOW YOUR SECRET.
MONTES: TO COACHING?

14:00.813 --> 14:02.757
ASHER: YES.
MONTES: HYDRATION.

14:02.858 --> 14:05.283
[CHUCKLES]
ASHER: SUCH A MONTES ANSWER.

14:05.383 --> 14:07.568
BILLY: OH, WHAT'S
HAPPENING HERE?
ASHER: COACH.

14:07.668 --> 14:09.652
BILLY: BEVERLY REUNION
IN THE HOUSE.
[ASHER CHUCKLES]

14:09.752 --> 14:11.898
MONTES: HEY, COACH.
BILLY: GOOD TO SEE YOU.
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

14:11.998 --> 14:13.421
SO, HOW'S, UH...

14:13.521 --> 14:14.864
HOW'S MY OLD OFFICE?

14:14.964 --> 14:16.828
JUST KEEP ADDING
BANNERS TO IT.

14:16.928 --> 14:19.634
I WAS JUST ASKING
MONTES HER SECRET
TO COACHING.

14:19.734 --> 14:21.639
WHAT'S YOURS?

14:21.739 --> 14:23.804
I'M NOT GIVING YOU
MY SECRETS.

14:23.904 --> 14:25.928
WE'RE RIVALS
NEXT YEAR, BRUH.

14:26.028 --> 14:28.173
YEAH.
ASHER: YEAH. I, UH,
I KEEP FORGETTING.

14:28.274 --> 14:30.418
[CHUCKLES]
BILLY: YUP.

14:30.518 --> 14:33.385
LOOK, UM...

14:33.485 --> 14:35.910
I WANT YOU BOTH
TO KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU'VE MEANT TO ME.

14:36.010 --> 14:38.877
YOU BOTH HELPED ME
BECOME THE PERSON
THAT I AM TODAY.

14:38.977 --> 14:40.881
NOW I'M--I'M
GONNA WALK AWAY

14:40.981 --> 14:43.206
'CAUSE I KNOW MONTES
HATES THESE MOMENTS.
BILLY: HA HA!

14:43.306 --> 14:47.095
I DO, BUT, UH,
THANK YOU, COACH ADAMS.

14:47.195 --> 14:49.139
ASHER: WELCOME.
BILLY: THANK YOU, SIR.
IT'S BEEN A PLEASURE.

14:49.240 --> 14:51.104
[CHUCKLES]

14:51.204 --> 14:52.988
SO THE RUMOURS
ARE TRUE.

14:53.088 --> 14:55.473
YOU AND ADAMS ARE GONNA
BE RIVALS NEXT YEAR?

14:55.574 --> 14:57.478
UH, YEAH, YEAH.

14:57.578 --> 14:59.883
I, UH, HAVEN'T...

14:59.983 --> 15:02.489
HAVEN'T TOLD
MY TEAM YET.

15:02.589 --> 15:04.974
DO YOU EVER THINK
ABOUT WHAT YOUR
NEXT STEP IS GONNA BE?

15:05.074 --> 15:08.261
BEVERLY IS
MY NEXT STEP.

15:08.362 --> 15:11.188
I MEAN, LOOK AT WHAT
WE GET TO DO.

15:11.288 --> 15:13.312
I LOVE THIS.

15:13.412 --> 15:15.758
AND THESE KIDS NEED US,
THEY LOOK UP TO US,

15:15.858 --> 15:17.762
AND THEY STILL LOVE
FOOTBALL.

15:17.862 --> 15:20.528
YOU KNOW,
SOME PEOPLE ASSUME
THAT I HAVEN'T APPLIED

15:20.628 --> 15:23.495
TO A D-1 JOB BECAUSE
I'M A WOMAN, BUT,

15:23.595 --> 15:27.944
REALLY,
IT'S BECAUSE...I'M
RIGHT WHERE I BELONG.

15:28.044 --> 15:29.388
HMM.

15:29.488 --> 15:31.432
DOESN'T GET
ANY BETTER THAN THIS,

15:31.532 --> 15:34.038
AND I'M SURE THAT YOU
HAVE YOUR REASONS
FOR MOVING ON,

15:34.138 --> 15:37.205
BUT...I'D BE CRAZY
TO LEAVE.

15:37.305 --> 15:40.612
SPENCER, VOICE-OVER:
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE
A GREAT COACH AT GAU,

15:40.712 --> 15:43.258
BUT YOU'RE A GREAT MAN
IN CRENSHAW.

15:43.358 --> 15:46.405
YOU'D BE INSANE
TO WALK AWAY FROM THAT.

15:48.292 --> 15:51.038
MALE RAPPER:
♪♪ STAY READY... ♪♪

15:51.138 --> 15:52.681
NICE GRAB, NICE GRAB,
NICE GRAB.

15:52.781 --> 15:55.167
YOU UP, CRAWFORD.
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

15:55.267 --> 15:57.492
SPENCE, SQUAD ABOUT
TO BE LEGIT NEXT YEAR.

15:57.592 --> 15:59.817
'BOUT TO GET
COACH BAKER HIS SECOND
STATE CHAMPIONSHIP.

15:59.917 --> 16:02.062
YOU UP, MAN. LET'S GO.
GO GET IT. GO GET IT.

16:02.162 --> 16:03.866
♪♪ AYE, GET OUT MY WAY ♪♪

16:03.966 --> 16:05.750
♪♪ I CANNOT BE STOPPED,
I'M RUNNING THE PLAY ♪♪

16:05.850 --> 16:08.316
♪♪ AYE, UH, GET OUT MY WAY,
I CANNOT BE STOPPED ♪♪

16:08.416 --> 16:10.761
[EDDY LAUGHS]
SPENCER: EDDY.

16:10.861 --> 16:13.246
COME HERE, MAN.
EDDY: HA HA HA!

16:13.346 --> 16:15.572
YO, SPENCE.
SPENCER: WHAT'S FUNNY?

16:15.672 --> 16:17.656
YOU OUT THERE DROPPING
EASY PASSES AND LAUGHING?

16:17.756 --> 16:19.500
WHAT'S FUNNY ABOUT
HAVING STONE HANDS, BRUH?

16:19.600 --> 16:21.304
YO, YOU AIN'T GOTTA DO ME
LIKE THAT, BIG DAWG.

16:21.404 --> 16:23.469
I DROPPED A PASS.
I'LL CATCH THE NEXT ONE.
NO BIG DEAL.

16:23.569 --> 16:25.794
NO, NO, IT IS A BIG DEAL.
IT AIN'T ABOUT

16:25.894 --> 16:28.841
THE DROPPED BALL, MAN.
IT'S ABOUT YOU SHOWING
ALL THOSE COLLEGE COACHES

16:28.941 --> 16:31.607
THAT YOU DON'T CARE.
LOOK, WE ALL KNOW
YOU GOT BIG TALENT.

16:31.707 --> 16:34.493
DO NOT GIVE THESE COACHES
A REASON TO PASS ON YOU,
MAN. COME ON.

16:34.593 --> 16:36.638
EDDY: YES, SIR.
SPENCER: LET'S GO.

16:39.364 --> 16:42.270
EVERYBODY, IT'S
SPENCER JAMES.

16:42.370 --> 16:44.355
HA HA HA HA!

16:44.455 --> 16:45.958
MAN, I JUST HAD

16:46.058 --> 16:48.163
A VERY SCARY FLASHBACK
TO YOU GETTING ON ME

16:48.263 --> 16:50.208
AT PRACTICE.
SPENCER: HEY,
IT WORKED, DIDN'T IT?

16:50.308 --> 16:52.212
OH...
SO YOU TAKING

16:52.312 --> 16:54.256
FULL CREDIT FOR MY
SCHOLLIE AT COASTAL?

16:54.356 --> 16:56.662
NAH.
NO, YOU EARNED THAT.

16:56.762 --> 16:59.067
MM, YOU DEFINITELY
HELPED, THOUGH.

16:59.167 --> 17:01.112
SPENCER: MM-HMM.
JABARI: THAT'S FOR SURE.

17:01.212 --> 17:03.156
MAN, YOU LUCKY.

17:03.256 --> 17:06.524
YOU GET TO BE REUNITED
WITH COACH BAKER
AT GAU NEXT YEAR.

17:06.624 --> 17:08.668
YEAH, BUT AT WHAT COST?

17:10.632 --> 17:12.176
LOOK, IF YOU ASK ME,

17:12.276 --> 17:13.779
COASTAL'S THE LUCKY ONE.

17:13.880 --> 17:15.984
THEY GOT THEMSELVES A STAR.
[JABARI CHUCKLES]

17:16.084 --> 17:18.470
BUT YOU KNOW WE GONNA
HAVE TO PLAY EACH OTHER
NEXT YEAR, RIGHT?

17:18.570 --> 17:20.514
YEAH, OCTOBER 7.

17:20.614 --> 17:22.559
YOU ALREADY KNOW
THE DATE?

17:22.659 --> 17:25.525
JABARI: OH, IT'S BEEN CIRCLED.
SPENCER: HA HA HA!

17:25.625 --> 17:28.852
JABARI:
YOU BETTER BE READY, MAN.
SPENCER: BOY, I STAY READY.

17:28.952 --> 17:32.500
JABARI: I HOPE SO.
HEY, GOOD TO SEE YOU, BRO.
SPENCER: PROUD OF YOU, MAN.

17:32.600 --> 17:34.425
HEY, THANK YOU.

17:34.525 --> 17:36.229
LET'S GO, 14.
SPENCER: AH!

17:36.329 --> 17:37.832
THERE YOU GO, THERE YOU GO.
JABARI: GOOD STUFF.

17:37.932 --> 17:40.097
THAT'S WHAT I'M
TALKING ABOUT, EDDY.

17:42.022 --> 17:44.927
MALE SINGER: ♪♪ CAN'T SAY
I HAD THIS PLANNED OUT ♪♪

17:45.028 --> 17:47.934
♪♪ EVERYWHERE I GO,
I STAND OUT ♪♪

17:48.034 --> 17:50.821
SADIE MOORE: TAMIA.
COOP: HEY, MS. MOORE.

17:50.921 --> 17:52.785
WHERE'S YOUR MUM?

17:52.885 --> 17:55.391
COOP: UH, SHE AIN'T COMIN'.
SADIE: WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

17:55.491 --> 17:58.037
I JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH HER. SHE TOLD ME TO
MEET HER HERE FOR COFFEE.

17:58.137 --> 18:00.803
I ASKED HER TO DO THAT
BECAUSE I KNEW YOU
WOULDN'T MEET WITH ME.

18:00.903 --> 18:04.571
TAMIA, I KNOW WHAT YOU
GONNA SAY, AND IT
AIN'T GONNA WORK.

18:04.671 --> 18:06.856
CAN WE PLEASE JUST
HAVE THE COFFEE?

18:06.956 --> 18:09.021
ALL RIGHT, I ORDERED
YOURS ALREADY.
SADIE: MM.

18:09.121 --> 18:10.664
AND THEN YOU CAN CALL
AND YELL AT MY MUM LATER.

18:10.764 --> 18:12.348
OH, I'LL CALL HER.

18:12.448 --> 18:14.493
SHE'LL PROBABLY BE
WAITING ON IT.

18:17.259 --> 18:19.123
SO...

18:19.223 --> 18:22.330
SHE TOLD ME YOU WERE
WORKING IN A LAW FIRM?

18:22.430 --> 18:24.254
YEAH. I AM.

18:24.354 --> 18:26.259
YOU HAVE REALLY TURNED
YOUR LIFE AROUND, HUH?

18:26.359 --> 18:28.424
I HAVE,
AND SO HAS PREACH.

18:28.524 --> 18:30.147
WE'RE MOVING
TO BALTIMORE, TAMIA.

18:30.248 --> 18:32.192
OK, BUT DON'T MOVE
BECAUSE YOU THINK

18:32.292 --> 18:34.757
YOU'RE PROTECTING AMINA
FROM HER DAD, ALL RIGHT?

18:34.858 --> 18:37.283
NOT UNTIL YOU GET
TO KNOW THE REAL PREACH.

18:37.383 --> 18:39.648
OH, I KNOW HIM.
I WATCHED HIM GROW UP.

18:39.748 --> 18:41.652
AND YOU WATCHED ME
GROW UP, AND YOU JUST SAID

18:41.752 --> 18:44.298
YOURSELF I WAS ABLE
TO TURN MY LIFE AROUND.

18:44.398 --> 18:47.124
WHY ARE YOU SO SURE
HE CAN'T TURN HIS AROUND?

18:52.817 --> 18:54.862
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

19:00.033 --> 19:01.937
YOU GONNA TALK TO HIM?

19:02.037 --> 19:03.581
I ALREADY DID
THE OTHER DAY.

19:03.681 --> 19:05.585
AIN'T NOTHING
LEFT TO SAY.

19:05.685 --> 19:07.870
IF THAT WAS TRUE,
YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

19:07.970 --> 19:09.514
I'M JUST HELPING OUT

19:09.614 --> 19:12.320
AND AVOIDING LIV.
GRACE: WHY?

19:12.420 --> 19:14.685
SPENCER: SHE WANTS
TO GET BACK TOGETHER.
GRACE: IS THAT A BAD THING?

19:14.785 --> 19:16.649
I DON'T KNOW YET.

19:16.750 --> 19:19.416
I MEAN,
WHAT'S REALLY CHANGED
SINCE WE BROKE UP, MA?

19:19.516 --> 19:22.502
YOU HAVE.
I MEAN, YOU'RE NOT
AS HAPPY, BABY.

19:22.602 --> 19:25.308
I'M JUST
ACKNOWLEDGING A FACT.

19:25.408 --> 19:28.195
[SPENCER INHALES, EXHALES]
GRACE: OK.

19:28.295 --> 19:30.279
I'MMA LET YOU
SIT WITH THAT,

19:30.380 --> 19:33.126
BUT AS FOR BILLY--
SPENCER: WHY'D YOU
FORGIVE HIM SO EASY?

19:33.226 --> 19:35.772
FIRST OFF, BILLY DIDN'T
NEED MY FORGIVENESS.

19:35.872 --> 19:38.377
I MEAN, I CONFRONTED HIM,
I SPOKE MY PIECE,

19:38.477 --> 19:41.584
WE'RE MOVING ON.
YOU AIN'T GONNA BE
DIVIDED FOREVER.

19:41.684 --> 19:44.591
SPENCER: LOOK, I TOLD YOU,
I ALREADY SAID MY PIECE, MA.
GRACE: DID YOU?

19:44.691 --> 19:48.339
'CAUSE IT SEEMS LIKE YOU
MIGHT HAVE A LITTLE MORE
THAT NEEDS TO BE SAID.

19:50.384 --> 19:52.328
[R&B MUSIC PLAYING]

19:52.427 --> 19:56.377
FEMALE SINGER:
♪♪ SOMETHING SO REAL ♪♪

19:56.477 --> 19:59.383
♪♪ YOU'RE MY LITTLE SWEET THANG ♪♪

19:59.484 --> 20:01.789
♪♪ YOU'RE MY LITTLE
SWEET THANG ♪♪

20:01.889 --> 20:06.359
♪♪ YOU'RE MY LITTLE SWEET THANG,
SWEET THANG, SWEET THANG ♪♪

20:06.459 --> 20:08.684
[SONG ENDS]

20:08.784 --> 20:10.969
[SIGHS]
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

20:11.069 --> 20:13.935
UM, IT'S GOOD.
IT'S GREAT.

20:14.036 --> 20:16.461
YEAH. THAT'S WHAT I
WANTED TO HEAR. HEH HEH!

20:16.561 --> 20:20.470
UM, NOW CAN I SAY
SOMETHING YOU MIGHT
NOT WANT TO HEAR?

20:20.570 --> 20:23.837
HEY, UM, I JUST FEEL
LIKE IT'S MISSING
SOMETHING.

20:23.937 --> 20:26.363
SOME OF THE LEVELS
ARE A BIT ROUGH.

20:26.463 --> 20:28.527
YOU KNOW, I'D--I'D JUST
GET RID OF THE FLUFF,

20:28.628 --> 20:30.692
AND IT FEELS A BIT
CROWDED. I DON'T THINK
YOU NEED TO FILL

20:30.792 --> 20:32.737
ALL THAT SPACE 'CAUSE
HER VOICE IS SO STRONG.

20:32.837 --> 20:34.100
MM. ANYTHING ELSE?

20:34.200 --> 20:35.984
UM, WELL, THE REVERB

20:36.084 --> 20:38.149
AT THE BEGINNING
HAS GOTTA GO.

20:38.249 --> 20:40.353
I MEAN, YOU COULD--YOU
COULD ADD SOME COMPRESSION
IN A FEW SPOTS

20:40.454 --> 20:42.558
OR TRY IT AND SEE
WHERE IT GETS YOU.
YOU KNOW, I MEAN,

20:42.658 --> 20:44.042
WE CAN EVEN ADD SOME
NOW IF YOU'VE GOT TIME.

20:44.142 --> 20:45.685
YES, PLEASE, YEAH.

20:45.785 --> 20:46.808
LAYLA: OK. DAD.
JP: HEY. THIS A BAD TIME?

20:46.908 --> 20:48.531
HI. UM, YOU KNOW

20:48.632 --> 20:50.416
SHAWN STOCKMAN.
JP: OH, HEY, IT'S BEEN A WHILE,

20:50.516 --> 20:52.260
BUT WE GO WAY BACK. COME ON.
SHAWN: GOOD TO SEE YOU.

20:52.360 --> 20:53.863
JP, CHUCKLING:
HEY, HEY.

20:53.963 --> 20:55.386
YOU KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
THIS GUY TURNED ME DOWN?

20:55.486 --> 20:56.830
UH, IT WAS NEVER
REALLY THE RIGHT TIME.

20:56.930 --> 20:58.914
JP: YEAH, RIGHT.
SHAWN: HA HA HA!

20:59.014 --> 21:01.360
JP: HEY, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?
SHAWN: ACTUALLY, I'M HERE

21:01.460 --> 21:03.765
TO TEST YOUR DAUGHTER OUT, MAN.
SHE'S MAKING A HELL OF A NAME
FOR HERSELF,

21:03.865 --> 21:05.569
AND NOW I BELIEVE
THE HYPE.

21:05.669 --> 21:08.014
LAYLA: SO YOU KNEW
WHAT WAS MISSING.
SHAWN: HEH!

21:08.114 --> 21:10.580
I DID, UM, AND I
NEEDED YOU TO HEAR
THE SAME THING,

21:10.680 --> 21:12.825
THAT IS, IF WE'RE GONNA
PRODUCE THIS SONG TOGETHER.

21:12.925 --> 21:16.553
WAIT. ARE YOU SERIOUS?
YOU--YOU WANT TO
PRODUCE WITH ME?

21:16.653 --> 21:18.076
SHAWN: LISTEN.
I'VE SENT THIS SONG

21:18.176 --> 21:20.482
TO ABOUT
20 PRODUCERS OR MORE,

21:20.582 --> 21:22.727
AND YOU KNOW HOW MANY
CRITICISED IT?

21:22.827 --> 21:23.969
JUST YOU.

21:24.069 --> 21:25.332
I DON'T NEED
SOMEONE TO TELL ME

21:25.432 --> 21:27.136
THAT THE SONG
IS GOOD.

21:27.236 --> 21:29.101
I NEED SOMEONE TO HELP ME
MAKE THE SONG GREAT.

21:29.201 --> 21:31.305
WELL, I'M IN,
AND I'M HONOURED. HEH!

21:31.406 --> 21:34.593
UM, DAD, CAN WE
TALK LATER? I'LL JUST--
JP: HEY, DO YOUR THING.

21:34.693 --> 21:36.357
HEY, SHAWN,
IT'S GOOD SEEING YOU, BRO.
SHAWN: GOOD TO SEE YOU, BRO.

21:36.457 --> 21:37.880
JP: ALL RIGHT. COOL.
SHAWN: ALL RIGHT. TAKE CARE.

21:37.980 --> 21:39.804
UM, OK. I JUST WANT
TO LISTEN TO IT

21:39.904 --> 21:41.889
ONE MORE TIME AND
THEN TRY SOME THINGS.

21:41.989 --> 21:43.492
SHAWN: YEAH. LET'S DO IT.
LAYLA: OK, GREAT.

21:43.592 --> 21:45.537
[INDISTINCT CHATTER,
WHISTLE BLOWS]

21:45.637 --> 21:47.140
OH.

21:47.240 --> 21:48.784
SPENCER: I GOT TO
GET GOING. YOU GOOD?

21:48.884 --> 21:50.788
YEAH, YEAH.
I'LL FIND A RIDE.

21:50.888 --> 21:52.793
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO.

21:52.893 --> 21:54.997
[SIGHS]
COACH, YOU GOT A SECOND?

21:55.098 --> 21:57.002
BILLY: YEAH.

21:57.102 --> 21:59.006
I GOT TO GET GOING.

21:59.106 --> 22:02.093
OK, WELL, UH,
THANKS FOR COMING OUT,

22:02.193 --> 22:04.338
HELPING WITH THE,
UH, WIDE RECEIVERS.

22:04.438 --> 22:05.621
APPRECIATE THAT.

22:05.721 --> 22:07.224
LOT OF TALENT
ON THIS FIELD.

22:07.324 --> 22:08.908
YEAH.

22:09.008 --> 22:11.113
IT'S GONNA BE
A BRIGHT FUTURE.

22:11.213 --> 22:13.859
LOOK, I STAND
BY WHAT I SAID.

22:16.024 --> 22:18.770
YOU'D BE CRAZY TO LEAVE
SOUTH CRENSHAW HIGH,

22:18.870 --> 22:20.774
BUT IF YOU'RE
GONNA DO IT,

22:20.874 --> 22:23.099
JUST RIP THE
BAND-AID OFF, MAN.

22:23.199 --> 22:25.144
WORKING WITH
YOUR PLAYERS TODAY,
THEY SO EXCITED

22:25.244 --> 22:27.148
ABOUT NEXT SEASON,
EVEN TALKING 'BOUT

22:27.248 --> 22:30.155
GETTING THEIR COACH
ANOTHER CHAMPIONSHIP.

22:30.255 --> 22:33.121
THEY GONNA TAKE IT HARD,
KNOWING YOU'RE LEAVING,

22:33.221 --> 22:35.166
AND THE LONGER YOU WAIT,
THE HARDER IT'S GONNA BE.

22:35.266 --> 22:38.172
I KNOW. I KNOW.
I, UH, WAS GONNA
TELL 'EM TODAY,

22:38.272 --> 22:40.778
BUT I THINK I'M GONNA
NEED A LITTLE BIT
MORE TIME

22:40.878 --> 22:43.103
'CAUSE MY HEAD'S BEEN
SWIRLING ALL AROUND.

22:43.203 --> 22:44.827
IT'S NEVER GONNA BE
THE RIGHT TIME.

22:44.927 --> 22:46.350
I KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE BLINDSIDED.

22:46.450 --> 22:48.555
DO NOT DO THAT
TO THESE KIDS.

22:48.655 --> 22:50.880
THEY GOT ENOUGH OBSTACLES
THEY GOTTA FACE.

22:50.980 --> 22:53.286
THEY DON'T NEED THE MAN
THEY LOOK UP TO MOST

22:53.386 --> 22:56.172
STRINGING THEM ALONG,
ACTING LIKE HE ALWAYS
GONNA BE THERE FOR 'EM.

22:56.272 --> 22:58.276
YEAH.

22:59.640 --> 23:01.684
SO WHAT ABOUT
YOU AND ME?

23:04.610 --> 23:06.916
I NEED TIME.

23:07.016 --> 23:08.920
I JUST NEED MORE TIME.

23:09.020 --> 23:11.024
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

23:13.149 --> 23:15.154
[SIGHS]

23:16.476 --> 23:18.381
COME ON, MAN!

23:18.481 --> 23:20.305
A.J.: BITCH, I WILL
RIP YOUR HAIR OUT.

23:20.405 --> 23:22.309
GIRL: GIRL, GET
YOUR HANDS UP OFF ME!

23:22.410 --> 23:25.196
[BOTH GRUNT]
PREACH: WHOA! WHOA! WHOA!

23:25.296 --> 23:28.443
WHAT THE HELL? I KNOW
Y'ALL NOT FIGHTING
IN MY HALLWAY!

23:28.543 --> 23:30.287
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?!
A.J.: DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

23:30.387 --> 23:31.890
I WAS JUST TAKING
OUT THE TRASH.

23:31.990 --> 23:33.735
LOOK, Y'ALL CAN'T BE
FIGHTING IN HERE.

23:33.835 --> 23:35.338
A.J.: THEN WE CAN GO OUTSIDE.
PREACH: LOOK, IF I REPORT

23:35.438 --> 23:37.503
THIS, YOU'RE BOTH
GETTING EXPELLED.

23:37.603 --> 23:40.269
A.J.: HEH! WE KNOW YOU
AIN'T REPORTING NOTHING.
PREACH: WHY WON'T I?

23:40.369 --> 23:42.113
MY BROTHER SAYS NOBODY
MESSES WITH PREACH.

23:42.213 --> 23:43.957
YOU WAS IN PRISON,
RIGHT?

23:44.057 --> 23:45.841
PREACH: SEE, WHAT YOUR BROTHER
SHOULD BE SAYING IS I'M

23:45.941 --> 23:47.926
AN EXAMPLE OF HOW SOMEONE CAN
TURN THEIR LIFE AROUND.

23:48.026 --> 23:49.529
IT AIN'T ABOUT
THAT LIFE NO MORE.

23:49.629 --> 23:51.333
I GOT
A DAUGHTER NOW,

23:51.433 --> 23:53.338
A FEW YEARS YOUNGER
THAN BOTH OF YOU,

23:53.438 --> 23:55.342
AND I'LL TELL HER
LIKE I'MMA TELL YOU.

23:55.442 --> 23:57.346
NO ONE CAN MAKE
YOUR LIFE EASIER,

23:57.446 --> 23:59.631
BUT YOU CAN MAKE IT
HARDER.

23:59.732 --> 24:01.636
A.J.: WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
PREACH: IT MEANS NOBODY'S GONNA

24:01.736 --> 24:04.602
OPEN THE DOORS FOR YOU,
BUT IF Y'ALL KEEP
ACTING LIKE THIS,

24:04.702 --> 24:08.050
THERE'S PEOPLE OUT THERE
THAT CAN'T WAIT TO CLOSE
THE DOOR IN YOUR FACE.

24:08.150 --> 24:10.575
LOOK, STOP ACTING LIKE FOOLS
AND STOP FIGHTING,

24:10.676 --> 24:13.442
AND YOU'RE GOOD.
NOW GET YOUR BAGS.

24:16.408 --> 24:19.154
ALL RIGHT, Y'ALL.
GATHER ROUND. BRING IT IN.

24:19.254 --> 24:22.161
BRING IT IN.
BRING IT IN.

24:22.261 --> 24:23.765
ALL RIGHT.

24:23.865 --> 24:25.849
HA HA HA!
LOOK AT Y'ALL.

24:25.949 --> 24:29.217
I GOTTA SAY, I'M PROUD
OF Y'ALL EFFORT OUT THERE.

24:29.317 --> 24:31.582
Y'ALL DID Y'ALL THINGS IN FRONT
OF THOSE COLLEGE COACHES,

24:31.682 --> 24:33.746
AND BELIEVE ME,
THIS WILL GO A LONG WAY

24:33.846 --> 24:36.192
TO BIGGER AND BETTER THINGS
WHEN IT COMES TO YOUR FUTURE.

24:36.292 --> 24:38.357
I HAVE NO DOUBT
THAT EACH AND EVERY ONE

24:38.457 --> 24:41.483
OF YOUR SENIOR SEASONS,
Y'ALL GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

24:41.584 --> 24:44.009
GIVE YOURSELVES A HAND,
ALL RIGHT?

24:44.109 --> 24:46.052
PLAYERS: YEAH.
BILLY: ALL RIGHT.

24:46.154 --> 24:48.018
UH, THAT BEING SAID,

24:48.118 --> 24:50.263
I KNOW THAT THERE HAVE
BEEN A LOT OF RUMOURS

24:50.363 --> 24:52.869
FLOATING AROUND
'BOUT MY FUTURE,

24:52.969 --> 24:55.594
AND I JUST WANTED Y'ALL
TO HEAR IT FROM ME.

24:55.694 --> 24:57.879
THOSE RUMOURS ARE TRUE.

24:57.980 --> 25:00.325
I HAVE BEEN OFFERED
THE HEAD-COACHING POSITION

25:00.425 --> 25:02.329
AT GAU,

25:02.429 --> 25:04.855
AND, UM--
AND I'VE ACCEPTED IT...

25:04.955 --> 25:07.501
PLAYERS: OHH...
BILLY: BUT HOLD UP, HOLD UP.
I AIN'T DONE, I AIN'T DONE.

25:07.601 --> 25:11.589
I HAVE ALSO BEEN DOING
SOME SOUL-SEARCHING
THE PAST COUPLE DAYS,

25:11.690 --> 25:13.795
AND, UH...

25:13.895 --> 25:16.601
AFTER SEEING WHAT Y'ALL
WERE DOING OUT THERE
ON THAT FIELD TODAY,

25:16.701 --> 25:19.126
WORKING HARD AS HELL
TO MAKE CRENSHAW

25:19.226 --> 25:21.091
A BETTER TEAM NEXT YEAR,

25:21.191 --> 25:24.658
I REALIZED I MADE
A MISTAKE. YEAH.

25:24.758 --> 25:28.467
SOMEBODY REALLY CLOSE TO ME
JUST TOLD ME THAT I WOULD BE
CRAZY TO LEAVE CRENSHAW,

25:28.567 --> 25:31.874
TO LEAVE THE MAN
THAT CRENSHAW MADE ME,
AND HE WAS RIGHT.

25:31.974 --> 25:35.643
JABARI: SO YOU STAYING, COACH?
BILLY: I'M SAYING I'M RIGHT
HERE WHERE I BELONG.

25:35.743 --> 25:37.847
PLAYERS: YEAH!

25:37.947 --> 25:40.473
WHOO!
[ALL CLAMORING]

25:46.446 --> 25:47.629
HEY, THINK FAST, OLD MAN.

25:47.729 --> 25:49.192
BILLY: MM. HA!
JORDAN: OOH!

25:49.292 --> 25:50.916
BILLY: "OLD MAN"? HA HA HA!
JORDAN: YEP.

25:51.016 --> 25:53.562
OOH, THAT'S
A LITTLE WOBBLY.

25:53.662 --> 25:54.885
BILLY: HA HA HA!
JORDAN: AND YOU'RE THE ONE

25:54.985 --> 25:56.408
WHO TAUGHT ME HOW
TO THROW A SPIRAL.

25:56.508 --> 25:58.413
OH, I'VE NEVER HAD
YOUR ARM, THOUGH.

25:58.513 --> 26:00.096
YEAH, BUT YOU HAD
SOME WHEELS.

26:00.196 --> 26:01.900
I DID HAVE WHEELS.

26:02.000 --> 26:03.905
YOU KNOW, THAT SPEECH
WAS A SURPRISE.

26:04.005 --> 26:06.109
OH, NOW, YEAH, I'M
SORRY ABOUT THAT, SON.

26:06.210 --> 26:08.875
NAH, COME ON.
YOU DON'T GOT TO APOLOGISE.

26:08.976 --> 26:11.080
I WILL BE FINE.
WHEN YOU LEFT BEVERLY,

26:11.180 --> 26:13.085
I HAD COACH MONTES,
AND THERE'S GONNA BE

26:13.185 --> 26:15.129
PLENTY OF COACHES
IN MY FUTURE,

26:15.229 --> 26:17.053
BUT ONLY ONE DAD.

26:17.154 --> 26:18.857
HA HA HA!

26:18.958 --> 26:20.822
YEAH.

26:20.922 --> 26:23.828
I ACTUALLY CHANGED
MY MIND

26:23.928 --> 26:27.075
IN THE MOMENT...'CAUSE I
HAD BEEN STRUGGLING

26:27.176 --> 26:29.681
WITH WHAT I WAS GONNA SAY
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS, AND

26:29.781 --> 26:33.409
THEN I SAW WHAT
THE BOYS WERE DOING OUT
THERE, AND I REALISED--

26:33.510 --> 26:36.055
- YOU'RE RIGHT WHERE YOU BELONG.
- YEAH.

26:36.155 --> 26:39.182
I LOVED HEARING THAT.
IT MADE ME HAPPY.

26:39.282 --> 26:42.189
LOOK...IF YOU WANT
TO RE-ENTER

26:42.289 --> 26:44.434
THE TRANSFER PORTAL,
I CAN MAKE A COUPLE

26:44.534 --> 26:46.518
OF CALLS
'CAUSE I FEEL LIKE I PUT
YOU IN A BAD POSITION.

26:46.618 --> 26:49.445
NAH, NAH, NAH.
I THINK I'M RIGHT
WHERE I BELONG, TOO.

26:49.545 --> 26:51.890
THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
YOU DO SEEM HAPPIER

26:51.990 --> 26:54.696
THAN I'VE SEEN YOU NOW
IN A LONG TIME.

26:54.796 --> 26:57.061
YEAH, LOVE CAN
DO THAT TO YOU.

26:57.161 --> 26:59.106
JORDAN: WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?
BILLY: COME ON, MAN.

26:59.206 --> 27:03.115
YOU HAVE THE WORST
POKER FACE EVER,
ESPECIALLY WITH ME.

27:03.215 --> 27:06.201
OH, THE BUS IS ABOUT
TO LEAVE. LOOK,
YOU TELL LAYLA...

27:06.302 --> 27:08.687
SHE OFFICIALLY
HAS MY APPROVAL.

27:08.787 --> 27:10.771
NOW, HOW DID YOU--
HOW DID YOU KNOW?

27:10.872 --> 27:12.615
I'M YOUR FATHER.

27:12.716 --> 27:14.259
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

27:14.359 --> 27:15.903
BRING IT IN.
LOVE YOU, TOO.

27:16.003 --> 27:17.667
- MM.
- OHH...

27:17.767 --> 27:19.270
- HERE YOU GO.
- SEE YOU IN A BIT.

27:19.370 --> 27:21.315
YEP. HIGH
AND TIGHT, NOW.

27:21.415 --> 27:22.958
HA HA!

27:23.058 --> 27:25.063
HA HA HA!

27:30.916 --> 27:33.501
FEMALE SINGER: ♪♪ BUT I KNOW
THIS IS SOMETHING ♪♪

27:33.602 --> 27:37.069
♪♪ SO REAL,
OVERTHINK... ♪♪

27:37.169 --> 27:39.074
HEY, YOU
STILL BUSY?

27:39.174 --> 27:41.479
[STOPS MUSIC]
HI. UM, I AM
ALWAYS BUSY.

27:41.579 --> 27:43.764
HOW DID YOU LINK UP
WITH SHAWN ANYWAY?

27:43.864 --> 27:46.209
LAYLA: A FRIEND OF A FRIEND.
JP: AND DID YOU TELL HIM

27:46.310 --> 27:48.414
YOU USED TO HAVE
A BOYZ II MEN POSTER
GROWING UP?

27:48.514 --> 27:50.379
LAYLA: UM...
JP: MM, NO.

27:50.479 --> 27:52.423
[BOTH CHUCKLE]
JP: LOOK, UM,

27:52.523 --> 27:54.467
LAYLA--
LAYLA: CLAY SAID NO, DAD.

27:54.568 --> 27:58.477
I TOLD HIM HE COULD HAVE
THE KEATING NAME BACK,
AND HE SAID NO,

27:58.577 --> 28:02.405
SO I KNOW YOU WANTED ME
TO FIX IT, BUT I CAN'T.
SORRY.

28:02.505 --> 28:04.249
JP: I'M GLAD.
LAYLA: YOU'RE GLAD I'M SORRY?

28:04.349 --> 28:06.013
NO, I'M GLAD YOU
COULDN'T FIX IT.

28:06.113 --> 28:07.697
HE DIDN'T DESERVE
OUR NAME ANYWAY.

28:07.797 --> 28:10.142
LAYLA: AM I MISSING SOMETHING?
JP: YOU KNOW,

28:10.242 --> 28:12.547
SOMETIMES
I FORGET YOU'RE
ONLY 19 YEARS OLD.

28:12.647 --> 28:15.193
YOU KNOW WHAT I WAS
DOING WHEN I WAS 19?
NOT THIS,

28:15.293 --> 28:17.197
NOT BUILDING
AN EMPIRE.

28:17.298 --> 28:20.204
I WAS WASHING DISHES
AT A 24-HOUR DINER.

28:20.304 --> 28:23.932
I MEAN, I WANTED
ALL THIS, BUT...
IT WAS JUST A DREAM.

28:24.032 --> 28:25.937
YOU NEVER TOLD ME
ABOUT THAT.

28:26.037 --> 28:28.222
CHECK IT OUT. HEH!

28:28.322 --> 28:30.026
- YOU SEE THIS OLD NAPKIN?
- YEAH.

28:30.126 --> 28:32.311
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
WHEN I WAS WORKING
AT THAT DINER,

28:32.411 --> 28:34.235
I DREW...

28:34.335 --> 28:37.041
THIS LOGO
FOR KEATING RECORDS.

28:37.141 --> 28:39.126
DAD, THAT--HEH!--
SHOULD BE IN A MUSEUM.

28:39.226 --> 28:42.533
YEAH, I MEAN,
UH, I WAS JUST TRYING
TO CREATE SOMETHING

28:42.633 --> 28:45.981
THAT WOULD LIVE,
YOU KNOW, AFTER I WAS
GONE AND IF I WAS LUCKY,

28:46.081 --> 28:49.549
I WOULD HAVE A CHILD
TO BE MY BLOOD LEGACY,

28:49.649 --> 28:52.355
AND THEN MY MUSIC
WOULD BE MY SOUL LEGACY.

28:52.455 --> 28:54.239
WELL, I RUINED
THAT PART.

28:54.339 --> 28:56.564
NO, YOU ARE THAT PART.

28:56.664 --> 28:59.250
YOU ARE MY LEGACY
IN EVERY FORM, LAYLA.

28:59.350 --> 29:01.775
I'M JUST SORRY
IT TOOK ME SO LONG
TO REALISE THAT,

29:01.876 --> 29:04.181
AND I'M GLAD
YOU GOT OUR NAME BACK

29:04.281 --> 29:06.185
BECAUSE NOW, MY BLOOD

29:06.285 --> 29:08.631
AND MY SOUL ARE
BACK UNDER ONE ROOF,

29:08.731 --> 29:11.677
AND YOU ARE GONNA TAKE
OUR KEATING LEGACY
TO LEVELS I COULD

29:11.777 --> 29:14.764
ONLY DREAM OF
WHEN I WAS WASHING
DISHES IN THIS DINER.

29:14.864 --> 29:16.909
THANKS, DAD.

29:29.536 --> 29:31.080
HEY.

29:31.180 --> 29:33.044
GRACE: HEY.
BILLY: THANKS FOR COMING TODAY.

29:33.144 --> 29:35.049
TURNS OUT I WASN'T
NEEDED HERE.

29:35.149 --> 29:38.055
YEAH, I, UH, MADE
A QUICK U-TURN.

29:38.155 --> 29:41.062
GRACE, CHUCKLING: CAN I ASK WHY?
BILLY: SPENCER.

29:41.162 --> 29:43.707
HE WAS RIGHT,
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

29:43.808 --> 29:45.391
HE USUALLY IS.

29:45.491 --> 29:47.356
HMM.

29:47.456 --> 29:49.961
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
TELL HIM THAT.

29:50.061 --> 29:53.329
YEAH. I'LL SEE YOU
BACK AT SCHOOL.

29:53.429 --> 29:55.935
YEAH.

29:56.035 --> 29:58.079
[SIGHS]

30:00.003 --> 30:01.907
[EXHALES]

30:02.008 --> 30:03.912
OK.

30:04.012 --> 30:05.515
ALL RIGHT, SPENCE.

30:05.616 --> 30:07.961
TIME TO SPEAK YOUR PIECE
ONE MORE TIME.

30:08.061 --> 30:10.787
[RINGTONE PLAYING,
PHONE VIBRATING]

30:25.620 --> 30:27.624
[SIGHS]

30:30.831 --> 30:31.735
HMM.

30:31.835 --> 30:33.780
SPENCER, ON VOICEMAIL:
OH, THIS IS SPENCER.
LEAVE A MESSAGE.

30:33.880 --> 30:35.785
HEY, SPENCE, UM,

30:35.885 --> 30:37.749
I KNOW YOU SAID THAT YOU...

30:37.849 --> 30:40.355
YOU NEEDED SOME TIME,
AND I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
THAT, BUT I JUST--

30:40.455 --> 30:42.800
I JUST WANT YOU
TO KNOW THAT...

30:42.900 --> 30:44.764
YOU WERE RIGHT.

30:44.864 --> 30:47.390
YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

30:49.955 --> 30:51.859
HI, DADDY.

30:51.960 --> 30:54.505
AMINA, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?
YOU KEEP RUNNING AWAY,

30:54.605 --> 30:56.751
YOUR GRANDMA'S GONNA MOVE
YOU OUT OF THE COUNTRY.

30:56.851 --> 30:59.937
SADIE: NO...
I WON'T.

31:01.821 --> 31:04.868
CAN I SPEAK TO YOUR DAD
ALONE, PLEASE?

31:09.559 --> 31:13.467
IT'S POSSIBLE
I MISJUDGED YOU.

31:13.567 --> 31:17.115
I TOLD YOU AMINA WOULD BE
BETTER OFF WITHOUT YOU,

31:17.215 --> 31:19.561
BUT I CAN SEE HOW MUCH
SHE NEEDS YOU.

31:19.661 --> 31:21.004
THANK YOU.

31:21.104 --> 31:23.008
BUT SHE NEEDS US, TOO.

31:23.108 --> 31:25.013
MY HUSBAND AND I,
WE LOVE HER MORE

31:25.113 --> 31:27.618
THAN ANYTHING
IN THIS WORLD.

31:27.718 --> 31:29.983
SHE'S ALL
WE HAVE LEFT.

31:30.083 --> 31:32.269
I KNOW.

31:32.369 --> 31:36.397
[GULPS]
SO, I, UH...

31:36.498 --> 31:38.402
I'M WILLING TO PROPOSE

31:38.502 --> 31:40.687
A SHARED-CUSTODY
AGREEMENT.

31:40.787 --> 31:43.333
REALLY? NO BALTIMORE?

31:43.433 --> 31:45.297
NO BALTIMORE.

31:45.397 --> 31:48.504
WE WERE THINKING
2 OR 3 WEEKENDS A MONTH?

31:48.604 --> 31:51.711
I'LL TAKE IT.
I'LL TAKE ANY TIME I
CAN HAVE WITH MY BABY.

31:51.811 --> 31:54.918
I WISH IT WAS MORE
THAN THAT, BUT I ACCEPT.

31:55.018 --> 31:57.323
NO, YOU MISUNDERSTOOD.

31:57.424 --> 31:59.328
WE WERE THINKING
THAT WE WOULD HAVE AMINA

31:59.428 --> 32:01.733
2 OR 3 WEEKENDS
A MONTH AND

32:01.833 --> 32:04.599
SHE'D LIVE WITH YOU,
FULL-TIME.

32:06.524 --> 32:08.528
[CHUCKLES]

32:19.392 --> 32:21.296
YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T
ALWAYS HAVE TO BE

32:21.396 --> 32:23.501
WORKING, MAN.
YOU CAN TAKE A BREAK.

32:23.601 --> 32:26.467
OH, IT'S--IT'S NOT WORK.
I'VE ALREADY FINISHED THAT.

32:26.568 --> 32:30.155
I'M WRITING OUT ALL
THE QUESTIONS I HAVE
ABOUT BEING A DAD.

32:30.256 --> 32:31.799
FOR REAL?

32:31.899 --> 32:33.403
I MEAN...

32:33.503 --> 32:36.129
UH, WELL,
I GUARANTEE YOU,

32:36.229 --> 32:37.572
EVEN I WON'T
BE ABLE TO ANSWER

32:37.672 --> 32:40.338
ALL THESE QUESTIONS
WE HAVE HERE.

32:40.438 --> 32:43.345
"WHAT AGE DO THEY
START WALKING?"

32:43.445 --> 32:45.069
WELL?

32:45.169 --> 32:49.318
UM, HONESTLY--HEH!--
I DON'T REMEM--ONE?

32:49.418 --> 32:52.124
I FORGET. 1 1/2, MAN?
NEXT QUESTION.

32:52.224 --> 32:54.569
"WHAT IS SWAD--"
I CAN'T READ
YOUR HANDWRITING.

32:54.669 --> 32:56.373
WHAT DOES THIS SAY?
"SWADLING"?

32:56.473 --> 32:57.937
"WHAT IS SWADLING?"
ASHER: UH, "WHAT IS SWADDLING?"

32:58.037 --> 32:59.861
"WHAT IS SWADDLING?"
WHAT THE HELL IS--

32:59.961 --> 33:01.825
WHAT IS SWADDLING?
ASHER: I HAVE NO IDEA.

33:01.925 --> 33:04.030
SSS. ALL RIGHT.
UH, FORGET THIS LIST.

33:04.130 --> 33:07.037
UM, YOU'RE GONNA
BE FINE, MAN. JUST--

33:07.137 --> 33:09.442
YOU'RE GONNA FIGURE
IT OUT ALL ON YOUR
OWN, JUST LIKE I DID.

33:09.542 --> 33:12.208
YOU'LL BE COOL,
TOTALLY COOL.

33:12.308 --> 33:15.215
ASHER: WAS IT SCARY?
BILLY: OH, HEH HEH!
IT WAS TERRIFYING,

33:15.315 --> 33:19.223
BUT IT'S WORTH IT.
IT'S WORTH IT. UM...

33:19.324 --> 33:22.831
I REMEMBER WHEN, UH,
LIV WAS A BABY,

33:22.931 --> 33:24.836
SHE USED TO DO
THIS ONE THING
WHERE SHE'D REACH--

33:24.936 --> 33:27.803
REACH OUT HER ARM
AND JUST GRAB A HOLD
OF MY EAR.

33:27.903 --> 33:30.809
AH, I USED TO LET HER
DO THAT FOR HOURS.

33:30.909 --> 33:33.615
SHE WAS PERFECT.

33:33.715 --> 33:36.822
YOU ASKED ME, UH,
WHAT THE SECRET

33:36.922 --> 33:39.829
TO COACHING WAS,
AND, UM...

33:39.929 --> 33:42.675
IT'S SIMPLE, MAN.
I JUST TRY TO ACT

33:42.775 --> 33:44.920
LIKE A FATHER TO THE
PLAYERS, YOU KNOW.

33:45.020 --> 33:46.965
LIKE, YOU ARE
ALL MY KIDS,

33:47.065 --> 33:49.570
AND TO BE HONEST...

33:49.670 --> 33:53.699
YOU WERE ONE
OF MY FAVOURITES.

33:53.799 --> 33:58.349
YEAH, JUST TRY TO BE
SOMEONE THAT THEY'D
LOOK UP TO, YOU KNOW?

33:58.450 --> 34:01.396
ALL YOU CAN DO IS
TRY TO POINT THEM
IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION

34:01.496 --> 34:03.521
AND HOPE THEY STAY
ON THAT PATH.

34:03.621 --> 34:05.806
YOU PUT ME ON
THE RIGHT PATH.

34:05.906 --> 34:08.592
I TRIED MY BEST
WITH ALL OF Y'ALL.

34:10.035 --> 34:11.939
YOU GOT A BIG HEART.

34:12.039 --> 34:13.944
YOU'RE A GREAT COACH,

34:14.044 --> 34:16.389
AND YOU'LL BE
AN EVEN BETTER FATHER.

34:16.489 --> 34:18.433
HOW LONG WILL IT TAKE
TO FIGURE IT OUT?

34:18.534 --> 34:21.079
AH, SEE, THAT'S
THE BEST PART
OF ALL THIS.

34:21.179 --> 34:23.725
IT DOESN'T MATTER
HOW LONG IT'S GONNA
TAKE TO FIGURE IT OUT

34:23.825 --> 34:27.594
BECAUSE THE ONE THING
YOU HAVE IS TIME.

34:29.438 --> 34:31.101
[BANG]

34:31.201 --> 34:33.206
[TIRES SCREECHING]

34:44.150 --> 34:46.155
[TIRES SCREECH]

34:50.243 --> 34:53.150
GRACE: OH, MY LORD.
JORDAN: I DON'T SEE MY DAD.

34:53.250 --> 34:55.515
GRACE: MAYBE YOU SHOULD
STAY IN THE CAR.
JORDAN: NO.

34:55.615 --> 34:57.519
THERE'S ASHER.

34:57.620 --> 35:00.165
JORDAN: ASH,
HEY, WHAT HAPPENED?

35:00.265 --> 35:01.809
ASHER: I DON'T KNOW.
GRACE: YOU'RE BLEEDING.

35:01.909 --> 35:04.735
ARE YOU OK?
ASHER: YEAH, I THINK SO.

35:04.835 --> 35:06.379
BILLY: OK, ALL RIGHT.
HERE WE GO.

35:06.479 --> 35:08.945
OK, TAKE IT
NICE AND EASY.

35:09.045 --> 35:10.829
GRACE: JORDAN!

35:10.929 --> 35:12.192
DAD!

35:12.292 --> 35:14.297
OH, YOU ALL RIGHT?

35:15.739 --> 35:18.165
OLIVIA: HEY, I'M HEADED OUT.
CHRISTEL: OK.

35:18.265 --> 35:21.332
OH, BEFORE YOU GO,
I HAVE SOME MORE NEWS.

35:21.432 --> 35:22.975
LET ME GUESS.
THEY WANT JAYDEN DAVIS

35:23.075 --> 35:24.859
TO DO THE "TODAY" SHOW?
CHRISTEL: CLOSE.

35:24.960 --> 35:26.503
THE ARTICLE'S
BEEN NOMINATED

35:26.603 --> 35:28.147
FOR A BARDO
JOURNALISM AWARD.

35:28.247 --> 35:29.550
OH, MY GOD.

35:29.650 --> 35:31.153
OH, MY GOD!
[CHRISTEL CHUCKLES]

35:31.253 --> 35:33.479
WAIT. BUT IF I WIN,
I CAN'T ACCEPT THE AWARD.

35:33.579 --> 35:37.527
WOMAN: CHRISTEL, WE'RE GETTING
SOME CONFLICTING REPORTS
ON A BUS CRASH.

35:37.627 --> 35:40.093
SOUNDS LIKE IT WAS
A FOOTBALL TEAM?
CHRISTEL: OK.

35:40.193 --> 35:41.697
WAIT. WHAT?

35:41.797 --> 35:43.301
W-WHERE WAS THE CRASH?

35:43.401 --> 35:45.505
LAURA: HELLO?
OLIVIA: HEY, WHERE ARE YOU?

35:45.605 --> 35:48.311
LAURA: I'M AT YOUR PLACE,
ACTUALLY. I JUST CAME BY

35:48.411 --> 35:50.997
TO GIVE COOP SOME GOOD NEWS.
OLIVIA: TURN ON THE TV,
CHANNEL 6.

35:51.097 --> 35:53.101
- WHY?
- JUST DO IT.

35:55.787 --> 35:59.095
MAN, ON TV: AS OF NOW,
WE STILL HAVE VERY FEW
DETAILS, BUT WE'RE HEARING

35:59.195 --> 36:01.941
A BUS CARRYING A HIGH-SCHOOL
FOOTBALL TEAM CRASHED.

36:02.041 --> 36:04.747
FIRST RESPONDERS ARE
STILL HAVING A HARD TIME
GETTING TO THE SCENE.

36:04.847 --> 36:08.315
LAURA: OH, MY GOD.
OLIVIA: MUM, I THINK
THAT'S DAD'S BUS.

36:08.415 --> 36:10.941
JUST STAY THERE. I'M ON MY WAY.
LAURA: OK.

36:14.909 --> 36:17.455
BILLY: ALL RIGHT.
MAKE SURE HE STAYS OFF
THAT LEG, ALL RIGHT?

36:17.555 --> 36:19.941
[RUBS PALMS TOGETHER]
OK.

36:20.041 --> 36:22.145
[EXHALES]
I THINK I GOT
EVERYBODY OUT.

36:22.246 --> 36:24.150
GRACE: YEAH. ARE YOU OK?
BILLY: YEAH, YEAH.

36:24.250 --> 36:26.235
I'M FINE. I'M FINE.
JORDAN: OK. DAD--

36:26.335 --> 36:28.079
BILLY: ASHER,
ASHER, HOW'S HIS ARM?
GRACE: UH, WE WRAPPED IT.

36:28.179 --> 36:29.642
HE'S DOING OK.
BILLY: OK.

36:29.742 --> 36:31.085
- DAD, DAD, MAYBE--
- YEAH?

36:31.185 --> 36:32.489
- MAYBE YOU SHOULD
SIT DOWN, REST.

36:32.589 --> 36:34.493
NO, NO, NO.
I'M GOOD. I'M GOOD.

36:34.593 --> 36:36.297
IT HAPPENED SO FAST.
IT ALL HAPPENED SO FAST...

36:36.397 --> 36:38.301
JORDAN: YEAH, THEY--
THEY SAID A TIRE BLEW OUT.

36:38.401 --> 36:40.546
WELL, I THINK I GOT
EVERYBODY OUT, THOUGH.

36:40.646 --> 36:41.869
GOT EVERYBODY OUT.
JORDAN: DAD. DAD?

36:41.969 --> 36:43.753
BILLY: YEAH?
GRACE: BILLY,

36:43.853 --> 36:45.477
IT'S OK.
BILLY: YEAH, YEAH.

36:45.577 --> 36:46.799
GRACE: EVERYTHING'S OK.
BILLY: OK.

36:46.900 --> 36:48.363
I'M GONNA GO
CALL SPENCER.

36:48.463 --> 36:49.767
BILLY: OK.
GRACE: YOU SHOULD CALL LAURA.

36:49.867 --> 36:51.289
SHE'S PROBABLY HEARD
ABOUT THIS BY NOW.

36:51.390 --> 36:52.853
OK. YEP.
THANK YOU.

36:52.953 --> 36:54.497
SPENCER.

36:54.597 --> 36:55.980
HEY.

36:56.080 --> 36:58.185
[EXHALES]

36:58.285 --> 37:01.553
I, UH, I CAME BY
EARLIER, BUT YOU
WEREN'T HOME.

37:01.653 --> 37:03.557
I FIGURED WE'D
HAVE THAT TALK.

37:03.657 --> 37:06.082
OLIVIA: WHAT?
SPENCER: YOU WANTED
TO TALK EARLIER,

37:06.182 --> 37:07.927
BUT I'VE SORT OF BEEN
AVOIDING YOU TODAY, SO--

37:08.027 --> 37:09.971
HAVE YOU NOT GOTTEN
YOUR MESSAGES?

37:10.071 --> 37:11.534
MY PHONE'S OFF. WHY?

37:11.634 --> 37:13.499
- MY DAD'S BUS CRASHED.
- WHAT?

37:13.599 --> 37:16.505
THE NEWS IS--IS SAYING
THEY THINK EVERYONE'S
OK, AND AMBULANCES

37:16.605 --> 37:19.111
ARE ON THEIR WAY, BUT
THERE WAS ANOTHER CRASH
ON THE FREEWAY, SO

37:19.211 --> 37:21.917
FIRST RESPONDERS AND EVERYTHING
ARE A LITTLE DELAYED.

37:22.017 --> 37:24.603
[RINGTONE PLAYING]
LAURA: OH! IT'S BILLY. IT'S DAD.

37:24.703 --> 37:26.847
BILLY!
BILLY: I'M OK. EVERYBODY--

37:26.948 --> 37:28.812
EVERYBODY'S OK.
LAURA: UH, AND HE'S OK.
EVERYONE'S OK.

37:28.912 --> 37:31.177
OLIVIA: WAIT.
PUT HIM ON SPEAKER.
LAURA: HOLD ON.

37:31.277 --> 37:32.701
DAD? DAD,
I LOVE YOU.

37:32.801 --> 37:34.545
I LOVE YOU, TOO, BABY.
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

37:34.645 --> 37:37.391
LAURA: WHAT HAPPENED?
BILLY: UH, THE TIRE BLEW OUT,

37:37.491 --> 37:40.518
AND THE BUS FLIPPED ON
ITS SIDE, BUT--BUT I'M OK.

37:40.618 --> 37:42.362
I'LL TELL YOU THE REST
WHEN I GET HOME,

37:42.462 --> 37:44.166
BUT I GOTTA TAKE CARE
OF MY PLAYERS, HONEY.

37:44.266 --> 37:46.171
OK. PLEASE JUST
HURRY HOME TO US.

37:46.271 --> 37:47.854
PLEASE COME HOME.
WE LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

37:47.954 --> 37:49.097
I LOVE YOU, DAD.

37:49.197 --> 37:51.101
YES.
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

37:51.201 --> 37:53.245
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

37:54.849 --> 37:56.353
ALL RIGHT.
EVERYBODY COOL?

37:56.453 --> 37:58.357
HOW Y'ALL DOING?
PLAYER: I'M GOOD, COACH.

37:58.457 --> 38:00.361
BILLY: ALL RIGHT.
PLAYER: STRAIGHT, COACH.

38:00.461 --> 38:02.366
WHERE'S JABARI?

38:02.466 --> 38:04.371
PLAYER: I DON'T KNOW.
DID YOU SEE HIM?

38:04.471 --> 38:07.016
WHERE'S JABARI?

38:07.116 --> 38:09.842
[BUS CREAKING]

38:15.134 --> 38:17.479
BILLY. DON'T!

38:17.579 --> 38:18.883
I HAVE TO.

38:18.983 --> 38:21.147
BILLY!

38:24.755 --> 38:26.259
LAYLA: HEY.

38:26.359 --> 38:28.303
SORRY.
I JUST HEARD.

38:28.403 --> 38:30.507
EVERYBODY'S OK,
THOUGH, RIGHT?

38:30.608 --> 38:33.033
COOP: YEAH. THEY'RE OK.
LAURA TALKED TO BILLY AND

38:33.133 --> 38:34.997
SPENCER TALKED TO GRACE.

38:35.097 --> 38:37.523
ASHER'S A LITTLE BANGED UP,
BUT HE'LL BE OK.

38:37.623 --> 38:40.569
LAURA: OH, I JUST
WANT HIM TO BE HOME ALREADY.
OLIVIA: HE'S GONNA BE HOME.

38:40.670 --> 38:43.055
HE'LL BE HOME SOON.
JUST BREATHE.
[LAURA SIGHS]

38:43.155 --> 38:47.064
LAURA: MM-HMM.
HE'S GONNA BE OK. YEAH.

38:47.164 --> 38:49.349
EXCUSE ME.

38:49.449 --> 38:51.955
[BEEP]
BILLY, ON VOICEMAIL: SPENCER,

38:52.055 --> 38:53.959
I KNOW YOU JUST SAID
YOU'D NEED MORE TIME,

38:54.059 --> 38:55.963
AND I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
THAT, BUT I WANTED

38:56.064 --> 38:58.649
TO LET YOU KNOW
THAT YOU WERE RIGHT,

38:58.749 --> 39:01.015
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

39:01.115 --> 39:03.661
YOU TOLD ME I'D BE CRAZY
TO LEAVE CRENSHAW.

39:03.761 --> 39:05.665
WELL, I JUST TALKED
TO MY TEAM,

39:05.765 --> 39:07.910
AND I TOLD THEM
I'M STAYING.

39:08.010 --> 39:09.955
THIS IS WHERE I BELONG,

39:10.055 --> 39:12.359
AND I KNOW
THAT DOESN'T UNDO

39:12.460 --> 39:15.005
WHAT'S HAPPENED BETWEEN YOU
AND ME, BUT I JUST

39:15.105 --> 39:17.411
WANTED TO TELL YOU
SOME THINGS.

39:17.511 --> 39:20.257
UM, ONE OF THE REASONS
I TOOK THAT JOB

39:20.357 --> 39:22.903
AT GAU WAS SO I COULD BE
YOUR COACH

39:23.003 --> 39:25.067
ONE LAST TIME.

39:25.167 --> 39:27.273
I MISSED IT.

39:27.373 --> 39:29.677
I MISSED YOU.

39:29.778 --> 39:31.923
OH, IT'S SELFISH,
I KNOW, BUT WHILE

39:32.023 --> 39:34.929
THIS PAST YEAR
AT CRENSHAW HAS BEEN GREAT,

39:35.029 --> 39:38.577
BEING YOUR COACH HAD BECOME ONE
OF THE BEST PARTS OF MY LIFE.

39:38.677 --> 39:40.943
WE HAVE A CONNECTION,
YOU AND ME.

39:41.043 --> 39:43.949
I KNEW IT THE SECOND WE MET
ON THAT FIELD AT SOUTH CRENSHAW,

39:44.049 --> 39:46.755
AND I KNOW I'M NOT
YOUR POPS, BUT...

39:46.855 --> 39:48.961
I DO CONSIDER YOU
MY SON.

39:49.061 --> 39:51.405
THAT'S WHY I'LL ALWAYS
BE HERE FOR YOU.

39:51.505 --> 39:53.410
PEOPLE ALWAYS TALK
ABOUT LEGACY,

39:53.510 --> 39:56.216
AND I KNOW
SPENCER JAMES IS GONNA CONTINUE

39:56.316 --> 39:59.463
TO BUILD HIS LEGACY,
BUT I NEED YOU TO KNOW

39:59.563 --> 40:03.873
THAT YOU ARE AN IMPORTANT PART
OF MY LEGACY.

40:03.973 --> 40:06.919
MY PROUDEST MOMENTS ON THE FIELD
AREN'T PLAYING BALL.

40:07.019 --> 40:09.887
THEY WERE COACHING YOU,

40:09.987 --> 40:12.613
WATCHING YOU GROW INTO
THE PLAYER YOU ARE TODAY

40:12.713 --> 40:15.398
AND THE MAN YOU'VE BECOME.

40:23.496 --> 40:28.447
FEMALE SINGER:
♪♪ I CAN FEEL YOU BREATHING ♪♪

40:28.547 --> 40:31.213
♪♪ IN THE HOLLOW
OF MY SKIN ♪♪

40:31.313 --> 40:34.299
BILLY, ON VOICEMAIL: YOU ARE
FAMILY, SPENCER, FOR LIFE.

40:34.400 --> 40:37.387
YOU CAN'T GET OUT OF THAT,
NO MATTER HOW HARD YOU TRY.

40:37.487 --> 40:40.353
YOU'RE STUCK WITH ME.
WE'RE GONNA GET PAST ALL THIS.

40:40.453 --> 40:43.500
SINGER:
♪♪ HERE WITH NO TOMORROW ♪♪

40:44.943 --> 40:48.731
♪♪ SORROW CREEPING IN ♪♪

40:48.831 --> 40:50.897
J?

40:50.997 --> 40:52.701
SINGER: ♪♪ GOING ♪♪
JORDAN: HE'S GONE.

40:52.801 --> 40:55.306
[OLIVIA WAILING]
SINGER: ♪♪ GOING, GOING ♪♪

40:55.406 --> 40:58.353
JORDAN: MY DAD IS GONE.
SINGER: ♪♪ GOING ♪♪

40:58.453 --> 41:00.758
♪♪ GOING ♪♪
BILLY: ANYWAY, I'M SORRY

41:00.858 --> 41:03.363
THIS MESSAGE GOT WAY TOO LONG,
BUT, UH, LIKE YOU,

41:03.464 --> 41:07.253
I HAD SOME THINGS
I NEEDED TO SAY AND, UH,
AND I'M GLAD I DID.

41:07.353 --> 41:09.257
UM...

41:09.357 --> 41:11.101
I LOVE YOU, SPENCER JAMES,

41:11.201 --> 41:12.905
AND I ALWAYS WILL.

41:13.005 --> 41:15.651
YOU ARE MY ALL-AMERICAN.

41:17.093 --> 41:19.639
SO, I KNOW YOU SAID
YOU NEEDED SOME TIME.

41:19.739 --> 41:22.646
UM, I'M HERE
WHENEVER YOU'RE READY,

41:22.746 --> 41:26.655
UH, BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,
YOU AND ME,

41:26.755 --> 41:29.461
WE GOT ALL THE TIME
IN THE WORLD.

41:29.561 --> 41:31.565
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

41:32.688 --> 41:35.555
SINGER:
♪♪ YOU'RE GONE ♪♪

41:35.655 --> 41:37.037
BACKGROUND SINGERS:
♪♪ GOING, GOING... ♪♪

41:37.138 --> 41:41.647
♪♪ GONE, GONE, GONE ♪♪

41:41.748 --> 41:44.695
- ♪♪ GOING, GOING, GOING ♪♪
- ♪♪ GONE, GONE ♪♪

41:44.795 --> 41:48.743
♪♪ GOING, GOING, GOING,
GOING, GOING ♪♪

41:48.843 --> 41:50.888
♪♪ GONE ♪♪
